## DECISIONS MADE (do not re-open)

- Flask prototype (figmaTem) annotation system is being MERGED into Next.js — Option A chosen
- Mobile-first from Day 1 — no desktop-first shortcut
- Phased feature rollout — no public roadmap promises, internal 6-month plan only
- Supplier relationships are FREE during beta — no commercial terms
- Batch sync for supplier catalog updates (not real-time) for MVP
- Scraping is best-effort — always implement graceful fallback to manual image URL input

---

## MVP SCOPE (Phase 1, 6-8 weeks)

IN:
- Image carousel with reference images
- Emoji annotation system (long-press 500ms → 8 emoji types → pin at x,y%)
- Product linking (tap pin → paste URL → scrape images → pick one → linked)
- Product panel filtered by active pins, grouped by emoji type
- Hierarchical projects (main → subprojects, 2 levels max)
- Role-based access: Architect / Contractor / Homeowner / Supplier
- Role-colored comments
- Curated reference catalog (~100-150 products)
- Categories: tiles/flooring, fixtures/hardware, lighting, cladding

OUT (Phase 2+):
- Pricing feeds
- Revit integration
- Supplier dashboard
- Automated scraping pipelines
- Real-time catalog sync
- Granular permissions
- Unlimited project nesting
- Custom emoji types

