## CURRENT PRIORITIES BY DEPARTMENT

### Tech
- Critical path: image carousel → emoji annotation → product linking → product panel
- Contract-first: Backend publishes API spec before Frontend builds anything
- QA baseline devices: Samsung A series (A14/A24/A54) and iPhone SE
- Performance targets: page load <3s on 3G, API p95 <500ms
- Known risk: long-press gesture conflicts with native mobile browser — test in Week 1

### Operations
- Deliver to Tech by Week 4: catalog Google Sheet (category, name, image_url, supplier_name, supplier_url)
- Deliver to Tech by Week 4: beta user list, Thai translation strings, 2-3 test project briefs
- Catalog labeling rule: "Reference" by default, "Available" only after supplier confirms
- Supplier onboarding: free beta, 2-min video tutorial, simple value prop
- Bug SLAs with Tech: P0 → 24hr triage, P1 → 72hr

### Marketing
- 90-day targets: 50 architects onboarded, 70% activation, viral coefficient >1.0
- Launch hook: "Pin your inspiration, link the perfect product, bring your vision to life — right from your phone."
- Channel priority: direct invite → LINE/WhatsApp communities → ASA → events → paid (Phase 2)
- Marketing owns: Awareness → Signup → first 24hr nudge
- Operations owns: Day 14+ onboarding and retention
- Deliver to Tech by Day 3: analytics tracking events spec (10 events)
- Deliver to Tech by Week 1: branding assets (logo SVG, hex, typography)

